<HEAD>Records Show City Official Runs Illegal Social Club</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Social Club Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The city's new commissioner of Hispanic affairs
operates an illegal social club that was ordered closed last year
and again <DATE>Monday</DATE> for safety and fire violations, city records show.
   Commissioner <PERSON>William Nieves</PERSON> runs the club, <LOCATION>El Caney</LOCATION>, in a
building that is supposed to be used as a factory, according to
city <ORGANIZATION>Buildings Department</ORGANIZATION> documents, the <ORGANIZATION>Daily News</ORGANIZATION> reported.
   Nieves, appointed to the <MONEY>$65,000-a-year</MONEY> commissioner's post
<DATE>Friday</DATE>, denies <ORGANIZATION>El Caney</ORGANIZATION> is a social club, calling it a ``place for
cultural events,'' but acknowledges knowing about fire and safety
code violations cited last year, the newspaper said in a story
published today.
   An ``order to vacate'' sign was posted on the club door <DATE>Monday</DATE>
by a mayoral task force that is cracking down on illegal
establishments in the wake of a fire at an illegal <LOCATION>Bronx</LOCATION> club
<DATE>Sunday</DATE> in which 87 people died.
   <PERSON>Nieves</PERSON> said he planned to give up his job as operator of <ORGANIZATION>El
Caney</ORGANIZATION>.
   ``It's not a bar or a social club. It's a place for cultural
events. ... When we have parties, they can serve liquor when they
have their own private activities. But you can't call that a bar,''
he said.
   <PERSON>Nieves</PERSON> said he had been under the impression repairs ``were the
responsibility of the landlord, not me.''
   The landlord, R&amp;R Real Estate, was unaware <PERSON>Nieves</PERSON> was operating
a social club there, the newspaper said.
   A summons issued by the <ORGANIZATION>Buildings Department</ORGANIZATION> <DATE>last April</DATE> cited
operation of an illegal gathering place without permits, lack of
emergency lighting, missing exit signs and unilluminated exit
signs. The summons cited a certificate of occupancy that lists the
building's function as a factory.
</TEXT>
